      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 337: 🔴 Critical Issues - `activePushCount` is decremented unconditionally in `onPushProcessed()`. If a push handler calls `onPushProcessed()` after an earlier failure, duplicate callback, cancellation path, or without a matching successful `onPushReceived()`, the counter can become negative. A negative value makes `releasePushHold()` think no push is in flight and can release the wakelock/foreground service while another push is still being processed. Clamp the counter and log the imbalance.\n\n```suggestion\nfun onPushProcessed() {\n    val remaining \u003d activePushCount.updateAndGet { count -\u003e\n        if (count \u003e 0) count - 1 else 0\n    }\n    if (remaining \u003d\u003d 0) {\n        Log.d(TAG, \"Push: no synchronous dispatches in flight\")\n    }\n}\n```",
