      "message": "[Critical] Line 55: 🔴 Critical Issues - Swallowing every `startForeground()` exception can hide a real foreground-service permission/type/configuration failure. On Android, if `startForegroundService()` was used and promotion fails, continuing as if the service is protected is unsafe and may still lead to process termination while push work is active. Handle `ACTION_PUSH_DONE` before promotion only when the service was not newly started, or at least log and stop the service on failure instead of silently continuing.\n\n```suggestion\n        } catch (e: Exception) {\n            Log.e(TAG, \"Failed to promote push service to foreground\", e)\n            stopSelf()\n            return START_NOT_STICKY\n        }\n```",
