      "message": "[Critical] Line 31: 🔴 Critical Issues - `onPushReceived()` reactivates accounts only when `daemon.isStarted`, but this call now happens before `ensureDaemonStarted()`. After an idle shutdown or cold push wake-up, the daemon may still be stopped here, so account reactivation is skipped and the subsequent native push dispatch can still race/drop the push. Move daemon startup before the push hold/reactivation step, or make `onPushReceived()` ensure startup before calling `setAccountsActive(... awaitCompletion \u003d true)`.\n\n```suggestion\nserviceScope.launch {\n    val app \u003d JamiApplication.instance as JamiApplicationFirebase?\n    try {\n        if (app !\u003d null) {\n            app.ensureDaemonStarted()\n            app.onPushReceived()\n            app.onMessageReceived(remoteMessage)\n        }\n    } catch (e: Exception) {\n        Log.e(TAG, \"Error in processing message\", e)\n    } finally {\n        app?.onPushProcessed()\n    }\n}\n```",
